description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
package subpackage;
public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
2. Compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\\Test.java

Observed Behavior: The test.class file is put in the subpackage\\subpackage directory. This means running the java command results in an exception:
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage.Test

Expected Behavior: The behavior should be the same as javac.

To fix the problem, the following command can be used: ajc -d .
